changing the capital stock by then end of <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">2001</TIMEX>. Losses in
flexibility occur when pollution control activities potentially
interfere with efficiency and other operational programs at a
regulated <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC_DESC">facility</ENAMEX>. Finally, there are interactions with the tax
system when, in response to a rise in the relative cost of
purchased goods, <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">people</ENAMEX> decide to enjoy more
